## Size Limits
| Type | Max Size | Notes |
|------|----------|-------|
| PDF | 200 MB | MITECO memorias can be huge |
| Non-PDF | 19 MB | DOCX/XLSX are smaller |
| Text output | 400K chars | PDF/OCR cap |
| Text/CSV | 300K chars | Direct text cap |

## Claude API PDF Constraints
- Rejects PDFs > 100 pages when sent as base64
- Fix: countPdfPages() + extractPdfText() for large PDFs
- **CRITICAL:** Truncating PDF bytes (slice) creates INVALID PDFs — use extractPdfText() instead

## Content-Type Ordering
Office MIME types contain "xml" — check Office formats BEFORE generic text/xml check:
```javascript
// WRONG: if (contentType.includes('xml')) → catches DOCX/XLSX
// RIGHT: Check officedocument/msword/ms-excel FIRST, then fall through to text/xml
```

## Async Extraction (Queue)
For files > 1MB:
```
POST /api/primitives/extract → creates extraction_job → enqueues to EXTRACTION_QUEUE
Queue consumer: processExtractionJob(jobId, env)
Poll: GET /api/primitives/jobs/:id → { status, progress_pct, total_chunks, completed_chunks }
Cancel: POST /api/primitives/jobs/:id/cancel
```

## Gotchas
- knowledge_docs column is `markdown` NOT `content` (caused SQLITE_ERROR on early versions)
- FileList is a live DOM reference — `Array.from(fileInput.files)` BEFORE any async work
- Geographic files (KML/SHP/KMZ/geojson/gpx) should be skipped, word_count=0
- fflate zipSync with compression on 30MB+ exceeds Cloudflare Workers CPU limit — use `{ level: 0 }` (store mode)
- DecompressionStream: 'raw' is NOT valid — use 'deflate-raw' for RFC 1951
- Strip trailing \r\n from stream bytes before decompressing
- Mistral OCR cost: $0.002/page. No page limit. No chunking needed.
- MISTRAL_API_KEY stored as Cloudflare Worker secret
